    <title>Preferences - Proxy</title>
    <p>
        The following image displays the Proxy preferences dialog:
    </p>
    
    <figure>
        <desc>The Proxy preferences dialog</desc>
        <media type="image" src="Images/preferences-proxy.png"/>
    </figure>
    
    <p>This dialog offers the configuration of a proxy.</p>
    
    <list>
        <title>The following options are available:</title>
        <item><p>Use a proxy for internet connectivity - Enable this option and fill out the HTTP Proxy and port fields, if you want or have to connect to the internet via a proxy. The default port for many proxies is 8080.</p></item>
        <item><p>Use authentication - Some proxies need authentication before they can be used. Enable this option and fill out the "Usename" and "Password" fields, if that is the case.</p></item>
    </list>
</page>
